title: Bug 4121: JarExporter causes out-of-sync (1GILQD5)
OB: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported JAR in the same directory (project), an out-of-sync message occurs when overwriting the exported JAR file for the second time.
EB: The JarExporter should handle overwriting the exported JAR file without triggering an out-of-sync message when placed in the same directory.
SR: Please address the issue with JarExporter to ensure smooth overwriting of exported JAR files without triggering out-of-sync messages.
